Striker Odion Ighalo is set to miss AFCON 2021 leaving the Super Eagles Nigeria with limited firepower to mount a formidable assault in Cameroon. Ighalo’s availability has made headlines in the lead-up to the AFCON 2021 that Cameroon is hosting from January 9 to February 6. “(Ighalo) is no longer expected as a result of issues with his Saudi Arabian club,” the Nigeria Football Federation is quoted by The BBC. Ighalo’s club Al Shabab has reportedly declined to release Ighalo stating that his invitation missed the deadline required to trigger his release for international duty.   Eagles holds first session in Garoua     Ighalo: Eguavoen laments     An interminable path to nationhood   The 32-year-old strikers’ absence is a further blow for Nigeria who will be without three other high-profile European-based options that withdrew due to health or administrative reasons. - Advertisement - Napoli hot-shot Victor Osimhen suffered a double-blow with Covid-19 and facial injury both ruling him out. Watford refused to release Emmanuel Denis while Paul Onuachu of Belgium club Genk is out due to injury. Three-time winners Nigeria kick-off their AFCON campaign on January 11 in the final-before-the-final Group D opener against record seven-time champions Egypt.